<h1>ICU Nurse Salary by State 2026</h1>
<p class="lead">Critical care nurses earn significantly more than the general RN average -- but the gap between the lowest and highest-paying states is nearly $50,000 per year. Here is the full breakdown by state, plus what actually moves your number.</p>

<h2>National ICU RN Salary Baseline (2026)</h2>
<p>The national median salary for ICU RNs in 2026 sits around $85,000-$92,000 base, with total compensation (including night differential, charge pay, and overtime) typically running $95,000-$115,000 for full-time staff nurses. Travel ICU nurses earn considerably more.</p>

<div class="box">
<strong>How to read this data:</strong> "Base salary" is your W-2 gross before differentials or overtime. "Total comp" includes standard differentials (nights, weekends, charge) but excludes overtime and bonuses, which can add another $10,000-$30,000 at high-overtime hospitals.
</div>

