<div class="highlight">
<strong>The income gap is real:</strong> An experienced MICU nurse choosing travel nursing over staff in a mid-range state is typically looking at $40,000-$80,000 more per year in gross compensation.
</div>

<h2>How to Negotiate a Higher ICU Salary</h2>
<ol>
<li>Cite your CCRN specifically as justification for the top of the posted range</li>
<li>Use competing offers -- even a travel nursing offer as a reference point shifts the conversation</li>
<li>Name your subspecialty experience -- CVICU, ECMO, or flight experience commands premium</li>
<li>Ask for a higher sign-on bonus instead of base when HR is inflexible on salary bands</li>
<li>Know the state average before you walk in -- hospitals rarely volunteer that they are below market</li>
</ol>

